label: other
naaccr_description: Other (intersex, disorders of sexual development/DSD). The word hermaphrodite formerly classified under this code is an outdated term.

label: Hispanic_Other
naaccr_description: Other specified Spanish/Hispanic origin (includes European; excludes Dominican Republic)

label: Unknown
naaccr_description: Unknown, indeterminate whether this tumor is present, not stated in patient record

label: Asian
naaccr_description: Other Asian, including Asian, NOS and Oriental, NOS

label: Asian
naaccr_description: Asian Indian or Pakistani, NOS (code 09 prior to Version 12)

label: Other
naaccr_description: American Indian, Aleutian, or Eskimo (includes all indigenous populations of the Western hemisphere)

label: Ambulatory >50pct
naaccr_description: Ambulatory more than 50 percent of the time, occasionally needs assistance

label: Ambulatory <50pct
naaccr_description: Ambulatory less than 50 percent of the time, nursing care needed

label: Managed Care, HMO, PPO
naaccr_description: Private Insurance: Managed care, HMO, or PPO

label: Medicaid Managed Care Plan
naaccr_description: Medicaid - Administered through a Managed Care plan

label: Medicare Managed Care Plan
naaccr_description: Medicare - Administered through a Managed Care plan

label: Medicare Managed Care Plan
naaccr_description: Medicare - Administered through a Managed Care plan

label: Disease-free
naaccr_description: Patient became disease-free after treatment and has not had a recurrence; leukemia in remission.

label: In situ invasive
naaccr_description: In situ recurrence of an invasive tumor.

label: In situ original
naaccr_description: In situ recurrence of an in situ tumor.

label: Local, insufficient info
naaccr_description: Local recurrence and there is insufficient information available to code to 13-17. Recurrence is confined to the remnant of the organ of origin; to the organ of origin; to the anastomosis; or to scar tissue where the organ previously existed.

label: Local invasive
naaccr_description: Local recurrence of an invasive tumor.

label: Trocar invasive
naaccr_description: Trocar recurrence of an invasive tumor. Includes recurrence in the trocar path or entrance site following prior surgery.

label: Local and trocar invasive
naaccr_description: Both local and trocar recurrence of an invasive tumor (both 13 and 14)

label: Local in situ
naaccr_description: Local recurrence of an in situ tumor.

label: Local and trocar in situ
naaccr_description: Both local and trocar recurrence of an in situ tumor.

label: Regional, insufficient info
naaccr_description: Regional recurrence, and there is insufficient information available to code to 21-27.

label: Invasive adjacent tissue only
naaccr_description: Recurrence of an invasive tumor in adjacent tissue or organ(s) only.

label: Invasive regional lymph nodes only
naaccr_description: Recurrence of an invasive tumor in regional lymph nodes only.

label: Invasive adjacent tissue and regional lymph nodes
naaccr_description: Recurrence of an invasive tumor in adjacent tissue or organ(s) and in regional lymph nodes (both 21 and 22) at the same time.

label: Regional in situ, NOS
naaccr_description: Regional recurrence of an in situ tumor, NOS.

label: In situ in adjacent tissue and lymph nodes
naaccr_description: Recurrence of an in situ tumor in adjacent tissue or organ(s) and in regional lymph nodes at the same time.

label: Multiple true for invasive tumor
naaccr_description: Both regional recurrence of an invasive tumor in adjacent tissue or organ(s) and/or regional lymph nodes (20-25) and local and/or trocar recurrence (10, 13, 14, or 15).

label: Multiple true for in situ tumor
naaccr_description: Both regional recurrence of an in situ tumor in adjacent tissue or organ(s) and/or regional lymph nodes (26 or 27) and local and/or trocar recurrence (16 or 17).

label: Distant, insufficient info
naaccr_description: Distant recurrence and there is insufficient information available to code to 46-62.

label: Distant in situ
naaccr_description: Distant recurrence of an in situ tumor.

label: Distant invasive peritoneum only
naaccr_description: Distant recurrence of an invasive tumor in the peritoneum only. Peritoneum includes peritoneal surfaces of all structures within the abdominal cavity and/or positive ascitic fluid.

label: Distant invasive lung only
naaccr_description: Distant recurrence of an invasive tumor in the lung only. Lung includes the visceral pleura.

label: Distant invasive pleura only
naaccr_description: Distant recurrence of an invasive tumor in the pleura only. Pleura includes the pleural surface of all structures within the thoracic cavity and/or positive pleural fluid.

label: Distant invasive liver only
naaccr_description: Distant recurrence of an invasive tumor in the liver only.

label: Distant invasive bone only
naaccr_description: Distant recurrence of an invasive tumor in bone only. This includes bones other than the primary site.

label: Distant invasive CNS only
naaccr_description: Distant recurrence of an invasive tumor in the CNS only. This includes the brain and spinal cord, but not the external eye.

label: Distant invasive skin only
naaccr_description: Distant recurrence of an invasive tumor in the skin only. This includes skin other than the primary site.

label: Distant invasive lymph node only
naaccr_description: Distant recurrence of an invasive tumor in lymph node only. Refer to the staging scheme for a description of lymph nodes that are distant for a particular site.

label: Distant invasive systemic only
naaccr_description: Distant systemic recurrence of an invasive tumor only. This includes leukemia, bone marrow metastasis, carcinomatosis, and generalized disease.

label: Distant invasive single site and local/trocar/regional
naaccr_description: Distant recurrence of an invasive tumor in a single distant site (51-58) and local, trocar, and/or regional recurrence (10-15, 20-25, or 30).

label: Distant invasive multiple sites
naaccr_description: Distant recurrence of an invasive tumor in multiple sites (recurrences that can be coded to more than one category 51-59).

label: Never disease-free
naaccr_description: Since diagnosis, patient has never been disease-free. This includes cases with distant metastasis at diagnosis, systemic disease, unknown primary, or minimal disease that is not treated.

label: Recurred but no other info
naaccr_description: Disease has recurred, but the type of recurrence is unknown.

label: Unknown if recurred or was ever gone
naaccr_description: It is unknown whether the disease has recurred or if the patient was ever disease-free.

label: Domestic Partner
naaccr_description: Unmarried or Domestic Partner (same sex or opposite sex, registered or unregistered, other than common law marriage)

label: Unknown
naaccr_description: Setting ASL to unknown since the purpose of language is one more source of inference on ethnicity and this is uninformative on ethnicity

label: Surgery Performed
naaccr_description: Surgery of the primary site was performed.

label: Surgery Not First Course
naaccr_description: Surgery of the primary site was not performed because it was not part of the planned first-course treatment.

label: No Surgery, Contra Indicated
naaccr_description: Surgery of the primary site was not recommended/performed because it was contraindicated due to patient risk factors (comorbid conditions, advanced age, etc.).

label: No Surgery, Deceased
naaccr_description: Surgery of the primary site was not performed because the patient died prior to planned or recommended surgery.

label: No Surgery, No Reason Given
naaccr_description: Surgery of the primary site was not performed; it was recommended by the patient's physician, but was not performed as part of the first-course therapy. No reason was noted in the patient's record.

label: No Surgery, Refused
naaccr_description: Surgery of the primary site was not performed; it was recommended by the patient's physician, but this treatment was refused by the patient, the patient's family member, or the patient's guardian. The refusal was noted in the patient record.

label: Unknown Whether Surgery Done
naaccr_description: Surgery of the primary site was recommended, but it is unknown if it was performed. Further follow-up is recommended.

label: Unknown Whether Surgery Recommended or Done
naaccr_description: It is unknown if surgery of the primary site was recommended or performed. Death certificate-only cases and autopsy-only cases
